<topic id="topic_5cg_y4y_wn">
  <title>rg.removeNode()</title>
  <body>
    <section>
      <title>NAME</title>
      <p>removeNode - Delete ReplicaGroup specified node.</p>
    </section>
    <section>
      <title>SYNOPSIS</title>
      <p></p><apiname>rg.removeNode</apiname>(<parmname>&lt;host></parmname>,<parmname>&lt;service></parmname>,<parmname>[config]</parmname>)
    </section>
    <section>
      <title>CATEGORY</title>
      <p></p>ReplicaGroup
    </section>
    <section>
      <title>DESCRIPTION</title> 
      <p>Delete ReplicaGroup specified node.</p>
      <parml>
        <plentry>
          <pt>host (string)</pt>
          <pd>Node hostname.</pd>
        </plentry>
        <plentry>
          <pt>service (string)</pt>
          <pd>Node port number.</pd>
        </plentry>        
        <plentry>
          <pt>config (json)</pt>
          <pd>Node configuration information.
            <parml>
              <plentry>
                <pt>Format</pt>
                <pd>Definition Format rg.removeNode() method has three parameters: host, service, config, as
                  shown above, the following format:</pd>
                <pd>("&lt;hostname>","&lt;port number>"[,{&lt;configParam>:value,...}])</pd>
              </plentry>
            </parml></pd>
        </plentry>        
      </parml>      
    </section>    
    <section>
      <title>Examples</title>
      <p>Delete node command follows ReplicaGroup shard.</p>
      <codeblock>rg.removeNode("vmsvr2-suse-x64",11800)</codeblock>
      <note><p>Delete the specified node must exist, otherwise abnormal.</p></note>      
    </section>
  </body>
